SIMPLE: responsive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Responsive
<hw>Re*spon"sive</hw> <pr>(-s?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>resposif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That responds; ready or
inclined to respond.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suited to something else; correspondent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The vocal lay <qex>responsive</qex> to the strings.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Responsible.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer.
Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*spon"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*spon"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Responsorial</ent>⟦br⟧
